                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote>Black majuscule letters against white background. Text between two ochre-coloured ruled lines. Character size varies. Ν, T, Ι in superscript. ΑΙ, ΤH, ΝΗΠ, ΤΙ, ΤΟ joined in ligature. In line 3 the ligature αΙ is written with a minuscule alpha attached to a majuscule iota. Mu in l. 4, with middle bar split into two parts, the upper part in the shape of an upsilon ending on a dot above a iota-shaped element; wide omega with crosslet in l. 9; use of diaeresis over iota in παντὶ (l. 5). Almost systematic use of accents and breathings. Double point after Ἀδελφοί and after ἀγαθόν. Letter height: <height unit="cm">4-5</height>
                            </handNote>
